1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,753
<i>My son had nothing</i>
<i>to do with what happened.</i>

2
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:07,007
<i>We didn't get any</i>
<i>information that could help us.</i>

3
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,134
<i>Reema sent me here to tell you.</i>

4
00:00:09,217 --> 00:00:10,301
<i>The owners have decided</i>

5
00:00:10,385 --> 00:00:13,304
<i>to suspend</i>
<i>your campaign with Grace & Glam.</i>

6
00:00:13,388 --> 00:00:15,932
<i>You wanted to be</i>
<i>a journalist when you were young, right?</i>

7
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,726
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- What happened?</i>

8
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,519
<i>What if I ruined her dream?</i>

9
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:21,604
<i>They didn't plan on having me.</i>

10
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:25,024
<i>Mama got pregnant</i>
<i>before finishing college.</i>

11
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>She wasn't able to pursue journalism.</i>

12
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:29,821
<i>I thought Mama was</i>
<i>okay with what happened.</i>

13
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:41,583
[theme music playing]

14
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:11,506
[eerie music playing]

15
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:20,765
- [music fades]
- [man] That was ages ago!

16
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:22,517
It's been a decade

17
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,311
but you still won't leave
Kyle alone because of Louisa!!

18
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,729
What more do you want?

19
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:30,108
Was humiliating him at school not enough?

20
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:31,234
Yes!

21
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:33,403
Because he threatened
to kill Louisa that day!

22
00:02:33,486 --> 00:02:34,863
- [tense music playing]
- That's why we're here today.

23
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:36,364
[scoffs] So, what?

24
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:39,242
You want to prove Edong's innocent?

25
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,828
And now you’re trying
to pin this on someone else?

26
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:46,207
Wow, Erica. You are still obsessed

27
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,960
with Lucas Santiago. Why?

28
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:51,754
Was he that good in
bed that you can't move on?

29
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:53,631
- [thud]
- [grunts]

30
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:58,553
Erica, tell your dog to back down.

31
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:01,764
Let go of me, you bastard!

32
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,516
- [phone buzzing]
- Marco.

33
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,852
- Let me go! Ow!
- [buzzing continues]

34
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:07,478
Love?

35
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,314
[Beth]<i> Love? Are you at home?</i>

36
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:11,107
No, why?

37
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:13,735
- Get off! I have a back injury!
- Marco!

38
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:15,194
Edong's at our home?!

39
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,529
[unsettling music playing]

40
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:17,780
- What?!
- [grunts]

41
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,827
[keys jingle]

42
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:31,169
[unsettling music crescendos]

43
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,671
[dogs barking]

44
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:38,551
[unsettling music resumes]

45
00:03:56,361 --> 00:04:00,990
[unsettling music continues]

46
00:04:07,288 --> 00:04:11,918
[music turns suspenseful]

47
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:36,484
- [door creaking]
- [suspenseful music continues]

48
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:42,782
[music crescendos]

49
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:55,461
[loud thud]

50
00:04:56,671 --> 00:05:01,634
[tense music playing]

51
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:25,074
[tense music continues]

52
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:42,884
[tense music continues]

53
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:46,554
[Beth] This is my stop.

54
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:54,979
[tense music intensifies]

55
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:56,939
Ma'am, you haven't paid yet!

56
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,275
Chloe?

57
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:00,651
Chloe? Sweetie?!

58
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,071
[Chloe screams]

59
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:04,363
- Chloe?!
- [screaming continues]

60
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:06,282
Chloe! Chloe!

61
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:09,243
- Aah! Aah! Aah!
- Chloe! Sweetie?!

62
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:10,453
Ma!

63
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:14,916
I'm here, sweetie. Mama's here.

64
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:19,212
[tense music crescendos]

65
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:21,964
Wow!

66
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,967
- I like that color.
- Really?

67
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,762
Why didn't you finish the purple one?

68
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:29,388
- Oh, yeah.
- [both chuckle]

69
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:35,895
Do you look like your sister?

70
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,817
Mm… I think, she's prettier.

71
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:44,070
I think you're pretty too, aunty Althea.

72
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:46,114
Aw! Thank you, Seth!

73
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:48,825
I think you're very cute and handsome!

74
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:51,160
I look like my daddy and mommy.

75
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,246
[chuckles] Yes, you do.

76
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:55,039
So cute! Get back to coloring.

77
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,333
Do you want other colors?
I have others here.

78
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,253
[crickets chirping]

79
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:16,686
[chirping continues]

80
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:25,111
[ominous music playing]

81
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:32,869
- [blow lands]
- [groans]

82
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:33,953
[body thuds]

83
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:42,879
[ominous music continues, fades]

84
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:47,758
[crickets chirping]

85
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:48,801
[Edward] Althea.

86
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:52,305
Come and help me with your Aunt Christina.

87
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:54,098
Sure thing, Uncle.

88
00:07:54,932 --> 00:07:57,268
Seth, I'll be back. Stay right here, okay?

89
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:00,688
There. Continue coloring that.

90
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:17,079
[sinister music playing]

91
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:21,042
[knocking on door]

92
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:34,680
Althea, let's play now.

93
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,766
[Althea] Give me a minute, Seth.

94
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,559
[sinister music continues]

95
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:54,408
[sinister music intensifies]

96
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:16,097
[sinister music continues]

97
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,767
[knocking continues]

98
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:29,735
[music becomes unsettling]

99
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:31,779
Bunny!

100
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:34,156
[Seth giggling]

101
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,369
Chloe! Love!

102
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:44,792
[Chloe sobbing quietly]

103
00:09:46,168 --> 00:09:47,336
Are you both okay?

104
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:51,257
[shudders, whimpering]

105
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:53,175
Did you see Edong?

106
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:54,844
Was he here?

107
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:56,846
[Marco] I'll check around the house.

108
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:58,973
Okay.

109
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,892
[sniffles, crying]

110
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:08,691
[unsettling music continues]

111
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:13,112
[creaking]

112
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:16,282
[screen door closes]

113
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,703
Why are you here?

114
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:26,417
[music becomes sinister]

115
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:29,462
Hello.

116
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:37,219
Hello.

117
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:42,558
[unsettling music resumes]

118
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,066
[door creaks closed]

119
00:10:55,696 --> 00:10:56,697
Seth?

120
00:10:56,781 --> 00:11:01,952
[unsettling music intensifies]

121
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:08,751
Seth?

122
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:09,835
Seth!

123
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:11,462
Seth!

124
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:18,511
- Seth--
- [Seth] No, no!

125
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:20,971
Mommy!

126
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:25,059
[unsettling music continues]

127
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:26,143
- [Seth] Mommy!
- [groans]

128
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:27,561
[Althea whimpers]

129
00:11:28,312 --> 00:11:29,563
- [Edong grunts]
- [thud]

130
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:32,024
Let me go!

131
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:34,819
[cries] Let me go!

132
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,363
Let me go!

133
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:41,367
[unsettling music crescendos]

134
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:47,164
Sweetheart. When you came home,

135
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:48,999
did you see Edong?

136
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,043
[sniffles, gulps]

137
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,463
[breathes shakily]

138
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,423
I didn't.

139
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,635
When I walked in,

140
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:02,054
it was already there.

141
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:05,141
[tense music playing]

142
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,059
Mama, was he responsible for that?

143
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:10,938
Why did he do that? Poor thing…

144
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:13,816
I'm going to kill that bastard!

145
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,152
I'm going to kill him!

146
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,319
[Chloe whimpers]

147
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:22,324
[tense music continues]

148
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:25,536
[Marco] Edong's nowhere to be found.

149
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:26,662
[Chloe sniffling]

150
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,790
[Erica] He had the chance to hurt Chloe.

151
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:31,709
But he didn't.

152
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,544
Why?

153
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,546
What does he really want?

154
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:41,469
[tense music continues, fades]

155
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:47,641
[engine rumbling]

156
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:49,894
[pensive music playing]

157
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,395
[Isla] <i>You were in a dark place.</i>

158
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:53,397
<i>Suffocating.</i>

159
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:55,274
<i>You were crying.</i>

160
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:56,609
[young Alice] <i>Mama!</i>

161
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,986
- [Isla] <i>And then what happened, Alice?</i>
<i>- </i>[young Alice] <i>Papa!</i>

162
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,199
[young Alice sobbing]

163
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:06,535
[footsteps approaching]

164
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:11,499
- [heartbeat pounding]
- [pensive music playing]

165
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,543
[Isla] <i>You're safe, Alice.</i>

166
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:17,296
<i>Even if that door opens,</i>

167
00:13:17,671 --> 00:13:18,589
<i>you are safe.</i>

168
00:13:18,672 --> 00:13:21,509
[heartbeat pounding faster]

169
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:22,551
[door opens]

170
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:25,137
[pensive music continues]

171
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:28,057
[breathing heavily]

172
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,768
<i>I don't get it!</i>

173
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,312
<i>Why is my body resisting this?</i>

174
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:34,647
<i>Breathe, Alice.</i>

175
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:38,317
<i>Your mind and body are</i>
<i>protecting you from a traumatic memory.</i>

176
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:40,069
<i>That's normal.</i>

177
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:42,530
[frustrated sigh]
<i>But time's running out for me.</i>

178
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:43,864
<i>I can't waste time on this.</i>

179
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:45,449
<i>My husband has to leave,</i>

180
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,660
<i>but he can't because of me.</i>

181
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:49,912
<i>All because I can't unlock my memory.</i>

182
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:53,040
[Alice sighs] <i>And you know what sucks?</i>

183
00:13:53,832 --> 00:13:55,626
<i>I still have to deal with this</i>

184
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,253
<i>while Edong is out there.</i>

185
00:13:57,336 --> 00:14:01,549
- [engine revving]
- [pensive music continues]

186
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:07,346
[birds chirping distantly]

187
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:10,140
[Scott] We're here.

188
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,103
Yeah.

189
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:15,938
[crickets chirping]

190
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,982
[tires screech softly]

191
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:20,985
[gearshift clicks]

192
00:14:21,068 --> 00:14:22,069
[Alice] What's that?

193
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:23,404
[car door opens]

194
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,322
[music becomes uneasy]

195
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,116
- [door closes]
- [panting]

196
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,200
[gasps]

197
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:32,454
[foreboding music playing]

198
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,125
Althea!

199
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:38,294
Althea, wake up!

200
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:39,587
Althea!

201
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:44,842
- [heart beating rapidly]
- [foreboding music continues]

202
00:14:44,925 --> 00:14:45,926
Seth!

203
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:47,803
- [Scott] Althea!
- Seth!

204
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,054
[objects clattering]

205
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,431
Seth? [sniffles]

206
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,266
Seth? [breathing heavily]

207
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:54,476
Seth?

208
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:58,105
Seth? [crying]

209
00:14:58,188 --> 00:14:59,315
Seth?

210
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,442
Seth?

211
00:15:01,525 --> 00:15:02,943
Seth? [crying]

212
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,905
- [objects thudding]
- [music fades]

213
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,950
[ominous music playing]

214
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:11,243
Auntie?

215
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,246
[sobbing, breathing heavily]

216
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:19,668
Auntie Christina, are you okay?

217
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,920
What happened?

218
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,589
[Christina whimpers]

219
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:24,715
Auntie.

220
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:26,926
Auntie, have you seen Seth?

221
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,386
[Seth] Let me go!

222
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,181
- [Edong] Shh.
- [Seth] Let me go!

223
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:34,934
- [suspenseful music playing]
- Let me go!

224
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:37,811
[Edong screaming in pain]

225
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:41,607
- [laughing mischievously]
- [Seth] Help! Help!

226
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,026
[Scott breathing heavily]

227
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:45,986
Where's Seth? Does she know?

228
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:48,989
Shit.

229
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,450
[suspenseful music continues]

230
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,577
[sobbing]

231
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,037
[both grunt]

232
00:15:56,997 --> 00:15:58,707
- [grunts]
- [cries]

233
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,418
- [dogs barking in distance]
- [Seth] Help!

234
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:03,963
- [laughing mischievously]
- [Seth] Let me go.

235
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:08,384
- [groaning]
- [Seth breathing heavily]

236
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:10,469
[muffled screaming]

237
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:15,557
[coughs, breathing laboriously]

238
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:22,064
- [dog barking distantly]
- [suspenseful music continues]

239
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:24,942
I will punish those who sin.

240
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:29,905
Including their children.

241
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:34,076
To the third and fourth generation.

242
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:39,748
- [Edward] Don't take the bible literally!
- [frustrated sigh]

243
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:45,754
[sinister music playing]

244
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,339
[thuds]

245
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,134
[Seth wheezes]

246
00:16:55,305 --> 00:16:57,057
Don't interfere.

247
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:01,353
You have nothing to do with this.

248
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:03,731
Give me my grandson.

249
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,608
And we won't have any problems.

250
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:10,070
[music becomes suspenseful]

251
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,865
[sinister music resumes]

252
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:13,949
[Alice] Seth?

253
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:16,493
[Alice] Seth?

254
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:20,706
Seth!

255
00:17:20,789 --> 00:17:25,919
[sinister music continues]

256
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:37,723
[suspenseful music sting]

257
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:40,559
Seth?

258
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:42,436
Seth!

259
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:46,023
[high-pitched tone plays]

260
00:17:46,106 --> 00:17:47,191
Seth!

261
00:17:48,275 --> 00:17:49,234
Baby!

262
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,196
[Susan] <i>We were at the market then.</i>

263
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:58,160
<i>Almost everyone helped searching for you.</i>

264
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:00,954
[sinister music continues]

265
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:03,874
- [breathing heavily]
- [dog barking in distance]

266
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,883
<i>Just wait for me, okay? Here, ma'am.</i>

267
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,551
[coins clinking]

268
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:18,055
- [coins clinking]
- [Susan] <i>Uh-oh!</i>

269
00:18:18,138 --> 00:18:22,684
[sinister music continues]

270
00:18:29,566 --> 00:18:31,610
Seth has nothing to do with this!

271
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:33,320
He's just a kid!

272
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:35,322
He's innocent!

273
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:41,036
[sinister music crescendos]

274
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:46,792
He's the beloved son of his mother.

275
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,129
The sin of his mother…

276
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:53,882
[unsettling music playing]

277
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:56,093
is also his sin.

278
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:02,599
I won't let you leave with him.

279
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:07,604
[snickering]

280
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:12,609
[laughing mischievously]

281
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:24,705
[unsettling music continues]

282
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:31,170
[both grunting]

283
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:32,296
- [knife swooshes]
- Ah!

284
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:42,848
- [Alice sobbing]
- [unsettling music continues]

285
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:48,937
Alice!

286
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:51,607
- [sniffles, crying]
- Alice.

287
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,400
What happened?

288
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:55,402
Are you okay?

289
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:58,572
Alice?

290
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,366
Are you alright?

291
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,286
[whispers] Yeah. [sniffles]

292
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:05,412
Yeah.

293
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:07,122
Yeah. I'm-- I'm fine.

294
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,540
Seth! [panicked breaths]

295
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,000
- We have to find Seth.
- Okay, let's go.

296
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:12,419
- We have to find Seth!
- Let's go! Let's go! Come on.

297
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:16,715
[tires screeching]

298
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:20,886
[ominous music playing]

299
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:23,722
[quivered breaths]

300
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:25,849
[dramatic music sting]

301
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:28,727
[panicked breaths]

302
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:29,686
[gasps]

303
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:33,607
[ominous music continues]

304
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:34,775
Althea!

305
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,904
I'll handle things here.
Go to Alice and Scott!

306
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:44,117
- Seth!
- Seth!

307
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,370
- Seth!
- Seth!

308
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:48,997
Seth!

309
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:52,876
[ominous music intensifies]

310
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,002
Seth!

311
00:20:57,881 --> 00:21:02,761
- [crowd chattering indistinctly]
- [ominous music crescendos]

312
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:05,264
<i>Did he kill someone again?</i>

313
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:07,099
[Scott] <i>This man… He's dangerous.</i>

314
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:08,642
<i>He'd hurt a child without blinking.</i>

315
00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:09,685
<i>Of course, you're coming with us.</i>

316
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:11,895
<i>But if I keep</i>
<i>running away, this won't end.</i>

317
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:13,939
[Beth] <i>I need to</i>
<i>protect my family right now.</i>

318
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:16,233
<i>I won't let Edong get anywhere near them.</i>

319
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:17,526
<i>We all need to come together.</i>

320
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:19,444
<i>We're all in danger.</i>

321
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,113
<i>Including our loved ones.</i>

322
00:21:21,196 --> 00:21:22,864
<i>We need to stop Edong.</i>

323
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:23,991
<i>[Erica] Since there's a witness,</i>

324
00:21:24,074 --> 00:21:25,951
<i>the police now believe</i>
<i>that Edong is still alive.</i>

325
00:21:26,034 --> 00:21:28,370
<i>Edong is here in</i>
<i>Amurao and he's not leaving</i>

326
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:30,789
<i>because everyone</i>
<i>he wants to exact revenge on is here.</i>
